      <title>Re: Is EQ good?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=228185#M228185</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The depth of EQ and the amount of content and quests really is quite awesome.  I do believe many of the old quests need to be revamped, as the reward for them for the effort can easily be better'd by something you can buy in bazaar for a few plat nowadays.  But still, if its doing the quest for the sake of questing, EQ certainly has enough of them.  As for graphics, they have been getting better and better, but considering the state of hardware and graphics capability provided by today's computers (and we are not necessarily talking state of the art hardware) the EQ graphics engine could use another upgrade.   I am currently testing beta software of other MMORPG games (wont mention here, NDA) and these are showing unbelievable graphic detail and quality (even full shadows!) with no or very very little video lag.  Even at full graphics capability, still very playable and just blow EQ graphics away.  Turning on shadows, even just enough to see the shadow only for the person standing next to you, should not bring my computer to its knees.  I know this for a fact after playing these others on my hardware.  I cant turn all the luclin full models on without a lot of lag in EQ. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Just saying they could do so much more with the graphics, but still give them an 'A' for effort and kudos for the revamps.  For just playability, yeah even after 7 years (started soon as EQ was originally released) EQ definitely has a lot of replayability.  I get tired of this character (I prefer to devote my attention to one main character at a time) I'll just make another race/class and start over!  =) &lt;/p&gt;</description>
