      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tanthulus, you're my hero. All valid points.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;--&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm kind of contrary to the norm, as I've defected *from* WoW to Everquest. I made the switch last week, and I have to say EQ is shaping up to be incredibly immersive for me. I started playing last friday night, averaging about 30 minutes a day. While it's not as 'polished' as WoW, it also doesn't have many of WoW's problems... specifically, it's community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For example, I just got through the tutorial. I'm level 10, I'm a human warrior, I'm about as 'newb' as you can get. The only way I found my way around PoK to do the tutorial quests was with CTRL+F. But more importantly, last night I entered my first true zone, Greater Faydark. The thing about that zone is that there's this city... a city in the trees. How do you get up there? A lift. How do you control a lift? Well... I had no idea really. I ask in OOC, and I got &lt;b&gt;three&lt;/b&gt; tells immediately, all of them telling me exactly how to go about it. By comparison, in World of Warcraft, if I had asked &amp;quot;How do I use the griffon master?&amp;quot; in general chat, the replies would have been something like &amp;quot;Omg you nubbles gt*o of this sservar&amp;quot;. That's about all the conversion factors you need to convert to EQ - the respectable people behind it's success.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;My toon on Stromm - Sanridil, 10 Human Warrior&lt;/p&gt;</description>
